Can't really complain. The app works like it's supposed to. I would only recommend just a little graphic design. It's a little bland using all default displays. Would also prefer the routines have extra fields if you're working two arms separately. I might not get as many reps out of my left as I do out of my right in something like, say, Lawnmowers. But there's only two fields, when their should be four since you repeat it. That's easily editable in the settings, though. But it is an extra step you might not notice right away to add, and can't during a routine. Would also like to see the non-worksheet routines added in by default (Ab Ripper is there, but it has no content). I did it manually, but others might not have the time create those separate routines. Really only suggestions, as the app is fully functional and pretty straightforward. Just couldn't hurt to have a few teaks. Kinda like a routine!

Follow the book to find out serving size.  No counting calories, just check off the box towards success!  First week I've lost one pant size.  Stay motivated, stick to the diet.  If you love chocolate like me, get the shakology to curb those cravings.  You can do this.

Other than that, it really is a pretty cool.app. The portion method food log takes some getting used to, but is nice.
